The paper proposes a new method for generating supervoxels in 3D space using visual saliency. This involves using computer vision techniques to identify salient regions in the input data and generating supervoxels in those regions. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also involves segmentation, which is a common topic in computer graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the use of saliency to guide the supervoxel generation process involves machine learning techniques, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves processing of 3D data, which is a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
